1. *Zida* se nova kuća na kraju ulice. (A new house is being built at the end of the street.)
2. Majstor je *zidao* zid od cigle. (The craftsman built a brick wall.)
3. Nisam mogao da se popnem na *zid*. (I couldn't climb the wall.)
4. Ova boja *zida* je predivna. (This wall color is beautiful.)
5. Danas ću da ofarbam *zidove* u sobi. (Today I will paint the walls in the room.)
6. Ćerka je ostavila crteže po *zidu*. (My daughter left drawings on the wall.)
7. On je visoko skočio preko *zida*. (He jumped high over the wall.)
8. Nisam siguran kako da popravim *zid* koji je oštećen. (I'm not sure how to fix the damaged wall.)
9. Na ovom *zidu* je oslikana mural umetničkog dela. (This wall is painted with a mural artwork.)
10. Postavio sam sliku na *zid* u dnevnoj sobi. (I hung a picture on the wall in the living room.)

Note: The word "zida" is a form of the verb "zidati" which means "to build" in English. The other forms of the word used in these sentences are: "zidao" - past tense of the verb, "zid" - noun meaning "wall", "zidove" - plural form of the noun meaning "walls", and "zidu" - locative case of the noun meaning "on the wall".